note right of Combatant
  Encapsulation: all combatant state is private
  and changed through behavior methods such as
  attack(), receiveDamage(), heal(), and addStatusEffect().
end note

note top of PlayerCharacter
  Inheritance: PlayerCharacter and EnemyCombatant
  specialize the shared Combatant abstraction.
end note

note bottom of Combatant
  Composition: Combatant owns value objects and
  registries that make up its lifecycle state:
  HitPoints, CombatStats, Inventory, and StatusEffectRegistry.
end note

note right of BattleAction
  Polymorphism: player choices, enemy turns, items,
  and special skills are executed through BattleAction.
  New actions can be added without changing BattleEngine.
end note

note right of StatusEffect
  Polymorphism: StatusEffectRegistry applies different
  effects through the StatusEffect interface.
end note

note right of BattleEngine
  Dependency inversion: BattleEngine coordinates the battle
  through abstractions such as TurnOrderStrategy,
  PlayerDecisionProvider, TurnProcessor, and WaveManager.
end note

note bottom of TurnBasedArenaGui
  Boundary-Control split: GUI and CLI classes handle input/output,
  while BattleController and BattleEngine coordinate use cases.
end note

@enduml
